<p>9. Pet Hotel may not in any case be held responsible for the action or omission of any other Client, even if this is liable to cause damages to another Client of the hotel. Any and all damages caused to third parties by Hotel Clients will be the sole responsibility of these and totally unrelated to Pet Hotel.</p>
<p>10. Pet Hotel does not assume responsibility towards the Client for any lost profits or indirect damages even if they result from the breach of the main obligation. </p>
<h4>XII. Notification duty</h4>
<p>In the event of theft or property damage or, in the event of fire, water damage or other damage to the hotel room, the Client must immediately inform the hotel staff and do everything possible to help with the resolution. of theft or to repair the damage.</p>
<h4>XIV. Termination of the accommodation contract</h4>
<p>1. Pet Hotel has the right to terminate the accommodation contract in the event that the Client does not pay the price in full and on time at the time it must do so or does not provide the required guarantee.</p>
<p>2. The Client may notify the termination of the accommodation contract during their stay at any time until 7:00 p.m., so that it takes effect from 12 noon the following day.</p>
<p>3. Any of the contracting parties may summarily terminate the accommodation contract for just cause.</p>
<p>4. Pet Hotel will have the right to immediately terminate the accommodation contract for just cause if the Client has any behavior that affects the healthy coexistence, calm or hygiene of the hotel, especially if during their stay at the hotel the Client is under the influence of drugs or alcohol, using the room for prostitution practices, acting offensively towards hotel staff or other hotel clients, disturbing the peace of other hotel clients or, in the past, have made malicious false reservations and / or damaged or destroyed the hotel or its facilities.</p> 
<h4>XV. Data Protection</h4>
<p>1. The Client is informed that their personal data will be stored and processed by Pet Hotel and are made available to the companies associated with Pet Hotel and selected service providers, in accordance with the Law, for the purposes of executing the contract, to services for the Client and for their own advertising campaigns.</p>
<p>2. The Client grants Pet Hotel the right to use associated companies and selected service providers to carry out data processing and the right to transmit such personal data under this section to companies that allow them to store and process.</p>
<p>3. The Client has the right to object at any time to the use of personal data for advertising purposes, for which he must demonstrate his intention in writing to Pet Hotel.</p>
<p>4. Unless there is legislation to the contrary, the Client's personal data must be discarded when the accommodation contract ends and the legal retention periods have expired.</p>
<p>5. Full details of the data protection policy can be obtained from Pet Hotel.</p>
